programme.title: Wimbledon Official Film '68
programme.desc: 'Wimbledon Official Film - Event Highlights'. A look back at some of the most iconic moments at The Championships

programme.title: Wimbledon Official Film '69
programme.desc: 'Event Highlights'. Rod Laver was the defending champion and won in the final against John Newcombe. Ann Jones defeated Billie Jean King in the final to win the Ladies' Singles tennis title at the 1969 Wimbledon Championships.

programme.title: Wimbledon Official Film '70
programme.desc: 'Wimbledon Official Film - Event Highlights'. A look back at some of the most iconic moments at The Championships. John Newcombe defeated his Australian countryman, Ken Rosewall.

programme.title: Wimbledon Official Film '71
programme.desc: 'Wimbledon Official Film - Event Highlights'. The highlight of the Ladies' singles was the final clash between Margaret Court and Evonne Goolagong, an all-Australian encounter.

programme.title: Wimbledon Official Film '72
programme.desc: 'Event Highlights'. Rain, the first of the fortnight, washed out Saturday play and for the first time in the history of The Championships, the men's final was played out on the Sunday to the dismay of traditionalists.

programme.title: Wimbledon Official Film '73
programme.desc: 'Event Highlights'. In Britain strikes had always been industrial disputes - until 1973 when most of the men's field at Wimbledon withdrew their labour in the most sensational move in the history of The Championships.

programme.title: Wimbledon Official Film '74
programme.desc: 'Wimbledon Official Film - Event Highlights'. Jimmy Connors defeated Ken Rosewall in the final to win the Gentlemen's Singles title at the 1974 Wimbledon Championships. Chris Evert defeated Olga Morozova.

programme.title: Wimbledon Official Film '75
programme.desc: 'Wimbledon Official Film - Event Highlights'. Arthur Ashe defeated Jimmy Connors in the final to win the Men's Singles tennis title at the 1975 Wimbledon Championships. Billie Jean King defeated Evonne Cawley.

programme.title: Wimbledon Official Film '76
programme.desc: 'Event Highlights'. Björn Borg defeated Ilie Nastase in the final. Reigning champion Billie-Jean King did not defend her title, as she had retired from singles play. Chris Evert defeated Evonne Cawley in the final.

programme.title: Wimbledon Official Film '77
programme.desc: 'Wimbledon Official Film - Event Highlights'. The 1977 Wimbledon Championships took place at the All England Lawn Tennis and Croquet Club. Björn Borg defeated Jimmy Connors and Virginia Wade defeated Betty Stöve in the final.

programme.title: Wimbledon Official Film '78
programme.desc: 'Event Highlights'. Bjorn Borg defeated Jimmy Connors in the final. Virginia Wade was the defending champion, but was defeated in the semi-finals by Chris Evert. Martina Navratilova won the title and first Grand Slam.

programme.title: Wimbledon Official Film '79
programme.desc: 'Wimbledon Official Film - Event Highlights'. Björn Borg defeated Roscoe Tanner and Martina Navratilova defeated Chris Evert-Lloyd in the final.

programme.title: Wimbledon Official Film '80
programme.desc: 'Event Highlights'. Björn Borg defended his title, defeating John McEnroe in the final. This final has been dubbed as one of the greatest matches of all time. Evonne Goolagong Cawley won the title, defeating Evert-Lloyd.

programme.title: Wimbledon Official Film '81
programme.desc: 'Wimbledon Official Film - Event Highlights'. John McEnroe defeated Björn Borg and Chris Evert-Lloyd defeated Hana Mandlíková in the final.

programme.title: Wimbledon Official Film '82
programme.desc: 'Wimbledon Official Film - Event Highlights'. Jimmy Connors defeated John McEnroe and Martina Navratilova defeated Chris Evert-Lloyd in the final.

programme.title: Wimbledon Official Film '83
programme.desc: 'Wimbledon Official Film - Event Highlights'. Jimmy Connors was the defending champion, but lost in the fourth round to Kevin Curren. John McEnroe defeated Chris Lewis in the final and Martina Navrátilová defeated Andrea Jaeger.

programme.title: Wimbledon Official Film '84
programme.desc: 'Wimbledon Official Film - Event Highlights'. John McEnroe was the defending champion and won in the final against Jimmy Connors. Martina Navrátilová defeated Chris Evert in the final.

programme.title: Wimbledon Official Film '85
programme.desc: 'Wimbledon Official Film - Event Highlights'. Boris Becker won the final against Curren becoming the first unseeded player and the first German to win the Wimbledon singles title. Martina Navrátilová defeated Chris Evert.
